!fyh:_ volgrids is a framework for volumetric calculations, with emphasis in biological molecular systems.

!def _smif_mode
    !fyh:path_in
        File path to a molecular structure e.g. a PDB file.
    !fyh:folder_out
        Folder path where the output grids should be stored.
        If not provided, the parent folder of the input structure file will be used.
    !fyh:path_traj
        File path to a trajectory file (e.g. XTC) supported by MDAnalysis.
        Activates 'traj' mode: perform the calculations for all the frames and save them as a CMAP-series file.
    !fyh:path_apbs
        File path to a cached output of APBS for the respective structure file.
        Prevents the automatic calculation of APBS performed by volgrids' smiffer.
    !fyh:path_chem
        File path to a .chem file to override the default macromolecules' table.
        Use this flag with an appropriate .chem file for running smiffer in "ligand" mode.
    !fyh:configs
        File path to a configuration file with global settings, to override the default settings (e.g. config_volgrids.ini).
        Alternatively, it can be a space-separated list of `configuration=value` keyword pairs for the global settings e.g. (`DO_SMIF_APBS=true DO_SMIF_STACKING=false`).
    !fyh:box
        Provide the box information that should be used to build the grids.
        Values must be passed in the following order: x_min x_max y_min y_max z_min z_max.
    !fyh:sphere
        Activate 'pocket sphere' mode by providing the X, Y, Z coordinates (sphere center) and the sphere radius R for a sphere.
        If not provided, 'whole' mode is assumed.
    !fyh:residues
        A string of space-separated residues for which to perform the calculations.
        The residues must be in the format "chain_id.resid" (e.g. "A.3 A.4 A.5 B.10").
        If not provided, all residues will be considered.
    !fyh:nproc
        Number of worker processes to use in trajectory mode (1 disables multiprocessing), default no multiprocessing.
        Frames are dispatched to workers and processed in parallel; output ordering may differ from frame order.
        Has no effect outside trajectory mode.
    !fyh:pack
        Use this flag to pack the output grids into a single CMAP file (with "all" as its SMIF kind in the file extension).
!fed

@smiffer
    !fyh:_ Calculate Statistical Molecular Interaction Fields (SMIFs) for biomolecular structures.
    !use:_smif_mode
!@

@smutils
    !fyh:_ Utilities related to more advanced SMIF usage.

    #### Utilities useful when running smiffer
    @res_nobp
        !fyh:_ Print the set of non-base-paired residues in a given RNA structure.
            A residue is considered non-base-paired if it does not form a canonical base pair (UA, CG) with any other residue.
            Requires rnapolis.
        !fyh:path_in
            File path to a molecular structure e.g. a PDB file.
    !@
    @res_nostk
        !fyh:_ Print the set of residues in a given RNA structure for residues that aren't participating in 2 stacking interactions.
            Requires rnapolis.
        !fyh:path_in
            File path to a molecular structure e.g. a PDB file.
    !@
    @chemgen
        !fyh:_ (experimental) Automatically generates a .chem file for a ligand given its 3D structure (e.g. PDB file).
            Currently only generates rows for stacking interactions, following a heuristic geometrical approach.
        !fyh:path_in File path to the molecular structure (e.g. PDB file) of a ligand.
        !fyh:path_out Path where to store the automatic .chem file.
            Defaults to path_in with extension ".chem".
    !@
    @sphere
        !fyh:_ Collection of utilities related to spheres in grids.
        @find
            !fyh:_ Get the sphere information (x,y,z,radius) for the smallest sphere that encloses all the atoms inside a selection query.
            !fyh:path_in File path to a molecular structure e.g. a PDB file.
            !fyh:query Query for selecting the atoms that will be enclosed by the sphere (MDAnalysis query format).
            !fyh:path_traj File path to a trajectory file (e.g. XTC) supported by MDAnalysis.
                When considering trajectories, the sphere information of each frame is concatenated together into a single space-separated string.
            !fyh:radius_extra Increment the radius of the returned sphere information by an optional amount.
        !@
        @grid
            !fyh:_ Create a grid with a single boolean sphere (optionally moving in time if a trajectory is considered).
                The grid encloses completely the provided structure file.
            !fyh:path_in File path to a molecular structure e.g. a PDB file.
            !fyh:sphere Sphere information in the format (x,y,z,radius), as provided by the "smutils sphere find" subcommand.
            !fyh:folder_out
                Folder path where the output grids should be stored.
                If not provided, the parent folder of the input structure file will be used.
            !fyh:path_traj File path to a trajectory file (e.g. XTC) supported by MDAnalysis.
                When considering trajectories, the sphere information of all frames must be provided into a single space-separated string.
        !@
    !@

    #### Advanced applications of the SMIF model
    @occupancy
        !fyh:_ Calculate occupancy grids (OGs) for biomolecular structures.
        !use:_smif_mode
    !@
    @pwoverlap
        !fyh:_ (experimental) Calculate point-wise overlaps between two biomolecular structures.
            Generates a CSV file with the overlaps.
            Currently only considers stacking interactions.
        !fyh:path_source Source molecule for the SMIF interactions.
            That is, the fields are centered around the atoms of this structure.
            [WIP] Currently only supports macromolecules, not ligands.
        !fyh:path_target Target molecule for the SMIF interactions.
            That is, this represents the "external" molecule that interacts with the source SMIFs.
            Every row of the output CSV file corresponds to a residue of this molecule.
            [WIP] Currently only supports macromolecules, not ligands.
        !fyh:path_out Path for the output CSV file.
    !@

    #### Miscellaneous
    @box_dim
        !fyh:_ Print information for the box that would enclose a molecular structure.
            Box information is printed as "x_min x_max y_min y_max z_min z_max".
        !fyh:path_in File path to a molecular structure e.g. a PDB file.
    !@
    @log_apbs
        !fyh:_ Heuristic transformation of APBS grids, useful for some visualization pipelines.
        !fyh:path_in Path to an APBS grid file (original or already processed by smiffer).
        !fyh:path_out Path where to store the resulting grid.
    !@
!@

@apbs
    !fyh:_ Generate raw APBS potential grids for biomolecular structures.
    !fyh:path_in Path of a molecular structure supported by pdb2pqr and APBS.
    !fyh:conv2mrc whether to store the output in MRC format (instead of APBS default DX format).
    !fyh:keep_pqr whether to keep the intermediary PQR molecular structure file.
    !fyh:verbose whether to display all the outputs produced by APBS.
!@

@vgtools
    !fyh:_ Miscellaneous tools for generic volumetric grids.
        Grids can be for any kind of data, not necessarily SMIFs.

    #### Operations for reorganizing grids
    @convert
        !fyh:_ Convert grid files between formats.
        !fyh:path_in Path of the grid to be converted.
        !fyh:folder_out Folder path where to save the output grid.
            If not provided, the parent folder of the input file will be used.
        !fyh:format Grid format in which to convert the grid.
            Supported formats: DX, BIN, MRC, CCP4, CMAP.
    !@
    @pack
        !fyh:_ Pack multiple grid files into a single CMAP series-file.
        !fyh:paths_in List of file paths with the input grids to be packed.
            At least one grid file must be provided.
        !fyh:path_out Path where to save the packed grid in CMAP format.
    !@
    @unpack
        !fyh:_ Unpack a CMAP series-file into multiple grid files.
        !fyh:path_in Path to the CMAP series-file to be unpacked.
        !fyh:folder_out Folder path where to save the unpacked grids.
            If not provided, the parent folder of the input packed file will be used.
        !fyh:format Grid format in which to unpack the CMAP file.
            Supported formats: DX, BIN, MRC, CCP4, CMAP.
    !@
    @extract
        !fyh:_ Extract the unique values of a grid file into separate files.
            In the case of a CMAP file, consider all values across all grids stored inside the file.
        !fyh:path_in Path to a grid file.
    !@

    #### Operations for transforming single grids
    @fix_cmap
        !fyh:_ Ensure that all grids in a CMAP series-file have the same resolution, interpolating them if necessary.
        !fyh:path_in Path to the CMAP file to be fixed.
        !fyh:path_out Path where to save the fixed CMAP file.
    !@
    @rotate
        !fyh:_ Rotate a grid file by 3 angles, along the xy, yz and xz planes (in degrees).
        !fyh:path_in Path to a grid file.
        !fyh:path_out Path for the rotated grid output.
        !fyh:x Rotation angle in degrees along the yz plane (in degrees).
        !fyh:y Rotation angle in degrees along the xz plane (in degrees).
        !fyh:z Rotation angle in degrees along the xy plane (in degrees).
    !@
    @segment
        !fyh:_ Segment the regions of space enclosed by a certain isovalue and save their cluster labels into a new grid.
        !fyh:path_in Path to a grid file.
            Must be in "BIN" format.
        !fyh:path_out Path for grid output with the cluster labels.
            The labels are integers starting from 1.
            The clusters are sorted in descending order by size (i.e. from largest to smallest).
        !fyh:isovalue Continuous voxels with an absolute value higher than this parameter will be considered part of the same cluster.
        !fyh:volume_thr Clusters with an amount of voxels lower than this parameter will be discarded from the resulting grid.
    !@

    #### Operations for combining multiple grids
    @average
        !fyh:_ Average all grids in a CMAP series-file into a single grid.
        !fyh:path_in Path to the CMAP series-file to be averaged.
        !fyh:path_out Path where to save the averaged CMAP file.
    !@
    @std_dev
        !fyh:_ Standard deviation grid for all grids in a CMAP series-file.
        !fyh:path_in Path to the CMAP series-file to be averaged.
        !fyh:path_out Path where to save the averaged CMAP file.
    !@
    @op
        !fyh:_
            Perform numeric operations between two grids.
            These are simple element-wise arithmethics (addition, substraction, multiplication, division), as well as absolute value for a single grid.
            They rely on numpy, so grids with mismatched shapes will be interpolated if needed (the second grid passed gets interpolated).
        @abs
            !fyh:_ Element-wise absolute value of the grid's points.
            !fyh:path_in Path to a grid file.
            !fyh:path_out Path where to store the resulting grid.
        !@
        @add
            !fyh:_ Element-wise addition of the grids' points.
            !use:_io_2_inputs
        !@
        @sub
            !fyh:_ Element-wise substraction of the grids' points.
                Order is "grid_0 - grid_1".
            !use:_io_2_inputs
        !@
        @mul
            !fyh:_ Element-wise multiplication of the grids' points.
            !use:_io_2_inputs
        !@
        @div
            !fyh:_ Element-wise division of the grids' points.
                Order is "grid_0 / grid_1".
                Dubious operation, as grids have usually many 0-valued points; make sure to preprocess the denominator grid appropriately.
            !use:_io_2_inputs
        !@
        @and
            !fyh:_ Element-wise AND of the boolean grids' points.
            !use:_io_2_inputs
        !@
        @or
            !fyh:_ Element-wise OR of the boolean grids' points.
            !use:_io_2_inputs
        !@
    !@

    #### Operations for inspecting/analyzing grids
    @summary
        !fyh:_ Print a summary of the grid file (format, dimensions, resolution, etc.) to the console.
        !fyh:path_in Path to a grid file.
    !@
    @histogram
        !fyh:_ Plot the distribution histogram of non-zero voxel values in a grid file.
            For multi-frame CMAP files, all frames are concatenated unless --key is specified.
            Percentiles (p50, p75, p90, p95, p99, p99.9) are printed to the console.
            Requires matplotlib.
        !fyh:path_in Path to a grid file (DX, MRC, CCP4, or CMAP).
        !fyh:path_out Optional output path to save the plot (e.g. .png, .pdf).
            If not provided, the plot is displayed interactively.
        !fyh:key Optional CMAP key (frame name) to plot a single frame instead of all frames.
    !@
    @compare
        !fyh:_ Compare two grid files by printing the number of differing points and their accumulated difference.
        !fyh:path_0 Path to a first grid file.
        !fyh:path_1 Path to a second grid file.
        !fyh:threshold Threshold for comparison.
            Points whose difference is higher than this threshold will be counted as "different".
    !@
    @points
        !fyh:_ Get the grid value(s) for specific XYZ point(s) in space.
            Grid values for every point are returned space-separated.
        !fyh:path_in Path to a grid file.
        !fyh:points (x,y,z) coordinates for the point(s) of interest.
            All values are to be provided space-separated.
            Must give at least 3 values (for a single XYZ point) or 3n values (where n is the number of points).
    !@
!@

!def _io_2_inputs
    !fyh:path_in_0 Path to a first grid file (defines target coordinate system).
    !fyh:path_in_1 Path to a second grid file (will be interpolated if needed).
    !fyh:path_out Path where to store the resulting grid.
!fed
